.
Did you know:
•Poor diets are partly responsible for more deaths than cigarettes globally?
•Studies show that frequent soda drinkers on average die 5 years earlier than non soda drinkers?
•Fast foods and processed foods are contributing factors to the #1 cause of heart disease?
•The number of new Type 2 Diabetes cases DOUBLES every year? (On average 80-90% of which are overweight or considered obese individuals)
•Healthy diet and frequent exercises can increase your chances of living a happier, longer, stronger life by 100%?
.
Let’s take care of ourselves 🙏🏽❤️
YOU DESERVE YOUR BEST LIFE!
.
Btw, those are an actual “soda abuser’s” teeth 😖
.

node.text:
Believe in YOU!
.
Happy Holidays everybody 🙏🏽 As this holiday season approaches, before the all the Black Friday, Cyber Monday and Xmas shopping chaos, my only wish is that YOU give YOURSELF the gift of self love and belief. Give yourself the gift of happiness. Give yourself the gift of acceptance. It doesn’t matter how big your crib is, how nice your car is or how much money you have in your bank account. When you’re truly, genuinely happy with yourself and who you are, you are the richest person alive. This is all I wish for you ❤️ All starts with believing in yourself. Because you can, and you will. Love is love.
-B

Transformation start with YOU!

This is a reminder that we are the cause of our own destruction. What we believe, we become. This goes for both negative beliefs and positive beliefs. Choose to be positive. YOU WERE MEANT TO BE HERE FOR A REASON.
.
YOU ARE POSSIBLE
YOU ARE LOVE
YOU ARE WANTED
YOU ARE STRONG
YES, YOU MATTER
AND YOU HAVE POWER
.
Start treating yourself right. You deserve it ❤️
#transformationtuesday

node.text:
I’ve been working with John Melo, CEO of Amyris, on a revolutionary new sweetener! Check this out to learn all about Purecane and our mission to eradicate obesity, diabetes, sugar addictions and all of the bad things sugar brings with this new incredible/all natural/sustainable/pure product!
.
So excited for Purecane and blessed for the opportunity to work with John as Amyris has been changing the world for the better already. Through fermented sugar cane, they created the number 1 Malaria treatment in the world and have saved the lives of over 1 million children with malaria PER YEAR since. We want to have that same impact with this all natural sweetener 🙏🏽

node.title: WE ARE CHANGING THE WORLD...in the sweetest way possible! 🍩🍫🍭

node.text:
Drop a 🙏🏽 for positive vibes!
.
Once you understand how powerful you are within, you exponentially increase the power and potentiality of everything outside of you. You don’t need to hear it from anyone else. Believe in you.
.
Hope you all have a positive, productive week!

Which one is crazier - 1 or 2?!
.
BOTH are try at your own risk 😂
.
A lot of my workouts are my own personal challenges to see if I can even do the stuff I come up with in my head. Your challenges may not look like this, but I encourage you to TRY YOUR THOUGHTS! You are so much more capable than you know. Hope you all have a happy, healthy and safe weekend 🤟🏽
.
Fit by @doyoueven

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Brandon Schram on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Drop a 💜 for Alzheimer’s Awareness!
.
Of all the shoots I’ve done, this is by far the one I hold closest to my heart. My Oma was diagnosed with Alzheimer’s which she eventually passed from, so this one was dedicated to her and and every other human out there battling this horrible disease. The goal was to depict the strength and the fight that Alzheimer’s patients put forth day in and day out, and I think @victoriagoretsky captured that beautifully 🙏🏽
.
Hope you are all having a happy and HEALTHY Wednesday! #alzheimersawareness

node.text:
Do you love or hate running?
.
Honestly I’m on both sides. Sometimes feels like OD work, but at the same time it’s completely freeing. More than any physical growth, longer distance running has given me incredible mental strength. You start to learn a lot about yourself when you’re a few miles out, shins hurtin, joints achin, muscles tight, and you know you can stop anytime…but you don’t. This was exactly how I felt my first half marathon. Got it done in 1:27 but felt like I had died and come back to life going through it lol. Oh yeah and RIP to that toenail on my second toe 😂
It might sound miserable to some of you but it really is liberating. Whether it’s running, walking, swimming, biking, whatever you do or try, PUSH YOUR LIMITS. You’ll surprise yourself with how resilient you are 💪🏽
.
Runners and socks by @doyoueven 💯
